	        				        				<h1 class="title">
	        					December 2012 Coffee News	        				</h1>
	        				        			
	        				        			
	        				        			
	        				        			
	        				        			
	        			<div id="node-816" class="node ntype-simplenews">

  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
          <div class="terms"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_17 first"><a href="../newsletter.1" rel="tag" title="">Recent Coffee News</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_3 last"><a href="../taxonomy/term/3" rel="tag" title="A monthly email NEWSLETTER with news of coffee specials, sustainable farming practices, the latest Velasquez Family Coffee news and much more. ">Velasquez Family News</a></li>
</ul></div>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <p>-Gathering Against the Dark<br />-Coffee Harvest Has Begun<br />-Spice it Up!<br />-VFC Out and About<br />-Holiday Gift ideas</p><p>On our oldest son's 18th birthday last month, we posted several baby pictures     to Facebook including&nbsp;a group shot of all of his cousins&nbsp;from his   first visit to Honduras.&nbsp;Since&nbsp;most of his cousins are now on   Facebook,&nbsp;we created a virtual reunion of sorts by tagging them in&nbsp;the     photo (which you can check out yourself on our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/VelasquezFamilyCoffee" target="_blank">Facebook Page</a>). The     holidays are a time of coming together in all kinds of ways and we celebrate   and   reflect on that below, give an update on the coffee harvest which is just   getting underway, and provide a few ideas for spicing up the holidays.   &nbsp;</p><p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Gathering Against the   Dark<br /></span></strong>When we first moved to&nbsp;Minnesota in 1991,&nbsp;not     only was Guillermo the sole member of his family here, but communication back     home was limited to a few letters a year and an occasional phone call   to&nbsp;his brother's work place since he was the only one in the family to have     a phone in Honduras&nbsp;back then. Truthfully it was pretty hard for Guillermo     to be that far from his family. Thankfully things have changed. These days, we     regularly chat with our nieces and nephews&nbsp;through Facebook and&nbsp;talk     by phone with his siblings and parents. Communications about coffee shipments     and payments happen via text and email. And&nbsp;several family   members&nbsp;have settled&nbsp;here in Minnesota&nbsp;and regularly stop by to     say&nbsp;hi. We're expecting a houseful when we all gather next on Christmas     Eve.</p> <p>As&nbsp;we approach the&nbsp;shortest day of the year&nbsp;and the darkness     of winter deepens, it makes sense that our habit is to gather together, perhaps     to hold off the darkness and give ourselves courage.&nbsp;As you gather&nbsp;in     the coming&nbsp;weeks with friends and family, consider how   you&nbsp;might&nbsp;make this a year long practice to join&nbsp;together with     others around the causes that concern you most. Here are just a few&nbsp;of our     favorite groups that give us hope and inspiration:</p> <p>*Addressing Climate Change --&nbsp;<a href="http://www.postcarbon.org/" target="_blank">Post     Carbon Institute</a>&nbsp;and <a href="http://350.org/" target="_blank">350.org</a><br />*Promoting Sustainable Farming -- in   Minnesota&nbsp;<a href="http://landstewardshipproject.org/" target="_blank">Land Stewardship     Project</a>&nbsp;and in Honduras <a href="http://www.sustainableharvest.org/" target="_blank">Sustainable   Harvest</a>&nbsp;<br />*Economic and Community Development --&nbsp;in Minnesota   <a href="http://www.ndc-mn.org/" target="_blank">Neighborhood Development Center</a> and around   the   world <a href="http://www.kiva.org/" target="_blank">Kiva</a><br />*Personal and Spiritual Growth     -- <a href="http://www.prospectparkchurch.org/" target="_blank">PPUMC</a>&nbsp;and <a href="http://aslaninst.com/" target="_blank">Aslan Institute</a></p> <p>Whether it be climate change, sustainable farming, violence, poverty or   something else, there are people already working together to make things better     and find a way forward. Add your energy to the growing circle and join in.</p> <p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Coffee Harvest Has Begun<br /></span></strong>The     news from Honduras is that the 2013 Coffee Harvest is under way. As the red   coffee berries ripen to a beautiful red over the next few months, they will be     hand picked, processed and then dried to await shipment to us. Honduras   continues to climb in worldwide coffee output industry experts say. However,     the&nbsp;spread of&nbsp;Coffee Rust (or "rolla") throughout Central   America&nbsp;could be a problem. We'll have more details about&nbsp;our own   family's harvest next month (so far "La Rolla" hasn't been a significant problem     for our farms thankfully). In the meantime, check out our photo <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/velaeber/sets/72157605181471604/" target="_blank">slide-show</a> of the coffee harvest process.</p> <p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Spice it Up!<br /></span></strong>As we expected,     our holiday flavors have been a hit. We've been selling lots and if you would     like to order any&nbsp;with your December order, we encourage you   to&nbsp;contact us quickly! The flavors that were chosen for 2012 are: <em>Wind     Chill</em>, <em>Gingerbread Spice</em>, <em>Drunken Uncle</em> and <em>Almond     Toffee</em>. All four of these flavors are available in&nbsp;8 oz packages,   whole bean and ground and in limited quantities of decaf for $6.50. Visit our     website for&nbsp;descriptions and details. Our <a href="http://www.vfamilycoffee.com/node/803" target="_blank">regular flavors</a> continue to     be&nbsp;available during this time as well.</p> <p>In addition to these coffees that come already flavored, we've had two   customers offer up flavoring tips you can do&nbsp;yourself. Trish says she adds     a few shakes of ground cardamom to the Maximo's French Roast in her coffee   grinder most mornings. Bonni adds half a stick of cinnamon to the Alma's Full     City Roast she grinds for her pot of coffee. Let us know&nbsp;if you have any     unique ways of spicing up your Velasquez Family Coffee.</p> <p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>VFC Out and About<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #000000;">We've been busy the past few months getting the word out about   our   coffee. On November 17, we enjoyed a very successful day at the <a href="http://www.doitgreen.org/" target="_blank">Green Gifts Fair</a>. For more local gift ideas     and green living resources, check out the <a href="http://www.doitgreen.org/directory" target="_blank">Do It Green Directory</a>&nbsp;and     the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.buylocaltwincities.com/giftguide" target="_blank">Buy Local Gift     Guide</a>.&nbsp;Nationally, we're proud to once again be in Green America's 2013     <a href="http://www.greenpages.org/" target="_blank">Green Pages</a>&nbsp;-- also a great source     for your holiday shopping. We were pleased to be featured in <a href="http://www.ediblecommunities.com/twincities/online-magazine/november-december-2012/november-december-2012-toc.htm" target="_blank">Edible     Twin Cities</a>&nbsp;Nov/Dec feature article on&nbsp;"The Buzz on Local Coffee."     And the <a href="http://www.parkbugle.org/" target="_blank">Park Bugle</a> featured our ad in     their holiday shopping guide.</span></p> <p>This coming weekend, there are two fun events where&nbsp;you can buy   Velasquez Family Coffee and do some holiday shopping:</p> <p>*<a href="http://www.piesandaprons.com/workshops.html" target="_blank">Holiday Happenings</a> by Pies and Aprons, 193 Pennsylvania Ave E, St. Paul, Friday, Dec&nbsp;7 (3-8),     Sat&nbsp;&amp; Sun, Dec 8 &amp; 9&nbsp;(10-4). A fun family event and holiday     market featuring vintage and upcycled goods, local handmade artists, organic   and   sustainable floral selections, live local music, drinks, and scrumptious pies     and food truck fare.&nbsp;Mini-workshops, Photos with Santa and Train rides   too!&nbsp;</p> <p>*Sibirica Boutique - 996 Oxford St. N, St. Paul, two weekends - December 8,     9, 15 &amp; 16&nbsp;from 10am-6pm each day. Featuring handmade gifts from   talented local artists.</p> <p>Finally, earlier this week, we sent out a promotional postcard to about 2000     people in two neighborhoods in St. Paul and folks are starting to respond. If     the postcard arrived at your house, feel free to pass it on to someone who might     be interested in our coffee. Referrals are our best source of new customers.</p> <p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>A Few More Gift   Ideas<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Of course, coffee also makes a great holiday gift. Buy   a   3, 6 or 12 month coffee gift subscription. Let us mail coffee to your family   and   friends. Order extras for those last minute gift giving needs. Read our <a href="http://www.vfamilycoffee.com/node/815#GIFTS">November Newsletter</a> for     more ideas.&nbsp;</span></span></p> <p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">And if you just     want inspiration for making the holidays simpler here are two great   resources:<br /></span></span><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">*This Green Life <a href="http://thisgreenblog.com/2012/12/green-your-holidays.html" target="_blank">Green Your   Holidays</a><br />*The Center for the New American Dream <a href="http://www.newdream.org/programs/beyond-consumerism/simplify-holidays/" target="_blank">Simplfy     Your Holidays</a></span></span></p><p><span style="color: #800000;"><strong>Housecleaning Help<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #000000;">If you could use help getting your house ready for the holidays   or   if you are looking for long term cleaning services,&nbsp;give our niece Cinthia     a call at 651-487-1231 or 651-285-3067 or email her at <a href="mailto:rodriguez20007@gmail.com">rodriguez20007@gmail.com</a><span style="color: #000000;"> for a cost estimate based on the size of your house and the   frequency of cleaning you need. </span></span></p> <p><em>As we end this email and this year, we want to take the opportunity to     thank you for the privilege of providing you with coffee. It brings us great   joy   to be creating connections and happy mornings over fine cups of coffee. Feliz     Navidad y Prospero Ano Nuevo!</em></p>  </div>
  
  
